                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/envr-401" class="program-course-title">
              ENVR 401 Environmental Research (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-25074" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: McGill School of Environment (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/610">School of Environment</a>)</p>
          <p>Administered by: <a href="/study/2014-2015/node/615">Faculty of Science</a></p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Environment              : Students work in an interdisciplinary team on a real-world research project involving problem definition, methodology development, social, ethical and environmental impact assessment, execution of the study, and dissemination of results to the research community and to the people affected. Teams begin defining their projects during the preceding spring.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Gregory Matthew Mikkelson, Julia Freeman, George McCourt (Fall)                  </p>

    
