                <h4>Field Course:</h4>

    
              <p>3 credits selected from the following courses or an equivalent Aquatic Field course: </p>
    
              <ul class="program-set">
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/agri-452" class="program-course-title">
              AGRI 452 Water Resources in Barbados (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-17480" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Bioresource Engineering (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/606">Agricultural &amp; Environmental Sciences</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Agriculture              : Physical environment challenges, centered on water, being faced by an island nation. Guest speakers, field study tours and laboratory tests. Private, government and NGO institutional context of conservation strategies, and water quantity and quality analyses for water management specific to Barbados.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
